summary: Carol Danvers: COULSON! Oh my god, it's been years since I've seen you! Last time I saw you, you were just starting out in...
body:
Carol Danvers: COULSON! Oh my god, it's been years since I've seen you! Last time I saw you, you were just starting out in SHIELD. What have you been up to lately?
Phil Coulson: Oh, not much. Well, I died but then got resurrected by Nick Fury. SHIELD then turned out to be HYDRA. I became director but went crazy for a bit. Then this Inhuman outbreak happened. Then I fell in love with someone named Rosalind Price, who got shot by one of my former agents who turned out to be a HYDRA agent. I killed him, then the founder of HYDRA possessed his body and came to Earth to destroy everything. Then after we dealt with him, I met Ghost Rider, who led us to this book of supernatural power called the Darkhold. A scientist named Holden Radcliffe used it to make Life Model Decoys, which then went crazy. And then I got kidnapped and put into something called the Framework, which was this digital recreation of the entire world, minus our biggest regrets. Then I made a deal with the devil to destroy the leader of the Life Model Decoys. And then after, I got taken to the future, where I learned the world was destroyed sometime in the past. When we got back to the past, we learned that the world was destroyed by Glenn Talbot, who absorbed a large amount of gravitonium to become Graviton. My daughter figure, Daisy, had to kill him to save the world. Also, I have a few days to live since the deal I made with the devil was at the cost of my own life.
Carol Danvers: ...
Phil Coulson: Oh, and I got together with Melinda May.

summary: I was trying to find the trailer for Captain Marvel, but got the trailer for the OTHER Captain Marvel. I was watching it...
body:
I was trying to find the trailer for Captain Marvel, but got the trailer for the OTHER Captain Marvel. I was watching it like, “…why is this so dark.. wait, Marvel? WHAT?”

I totally forgot that DC always uses SHAZAM! Ah, things get complicated when names overlap…

Anyway, I think Shazam looks freakin’ adorable and so far I’m gonna watch it. I’d like to see something light hearted from DC for once. They’ve been so angst ridden.. and then there’s that Teen Titans abomination they’re releasing… yikes..

summary:
West Coast Avengers #1 and The Life of Captain Marvel #2 were sooooo good this week
WCA was genuinely so funny and is shaping up...
body:
West Coast Avengers #1 and The Life of Captain Marvel #2 were sooooo good this week

WCA was genuinely so funny and is shaping up to be a good team book. All of their dynamics are so fun to read. Fave scene was probably the interviews for the team:

On the other hand, Captain Marvel was really touching. I’m enjoying how personal this story is without it being a full on origin story. We’re really getting to the heart of Carol’s strength of character, which honestly is hitting pretty close to home for me. Fave scene was Carol attending her dad’s funeral:

Close second was Carol going into space and literally punching the moon in frustration (her family situation is such a shit show omg):

summary: So, hear me out on this one. I doubt I’m the first to suggest that Gotham City has some Cthulhu Mythos stuff going on (what with...
caption:
So, hear me out on this one.

I doubt I’m the first to suggest that Gotham City has some Cthulhu Mythos stuff going on (what with Arkham Asylum and the strange pall cast over the city). So, what if –

A young boy named Wilbur Watson sleeps in the Gotham subway (Wang Enterprises can’t help everyone), and he is approached by a tall, shadowed stranger? What if –

That tall, shadowed stranger takes him on a mysterious train past seventy-seven stations to a temple where two priests, Nasht and Kaman-Thah, tend a sacred fire? And what if –

They empower the boy with the ancient phrase, CHDAN-YN, giving him the serenity of Cthulhu, the secrets of Hastur, the compassion of Dagon, the power of Azathoth, the triumph of Nodens, the universality of Yog-Sothoth, and the cunning of Nyarlathotep?

One thing is for sure: it would be a marvel.

(Also, since @titleknown has pointed out that Captain Marvel straddles the boundaries of the public domain, I might be able to actually do stuff with this concept that I couldn’t with the rest of the Theverse.)
